<span id="freeTextContainer1417325463791738236">No. Just, no.<br/><br/>I had pretty much decided to abandon this book unfinished when I received notification that the audiobook I had requested from the library was now available for download. Well, that clinched it. <br/><br/>And so, in the style of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32929.Goodnight_Moon' title='Goodnight Moon by Margaret Wise Brown' rel='nofollow noopener'>Goodnight Moon</a>, I am bidding this book good-bye. Good-bye book. Good-bye hopelessly twee title (which should have been a clue). Good-bye awkward dialogue, and good-bye emotional manipulation. Good-bye, poor cliched struggling immigrant adolescent Henry. Good-bye, clea</span>
  <span id="freeText1417325463791738236" style="display:none">No. Just, no.<br /><br />I had pretty much decided to abandon this book unfinished when I received notification that the audiobook I had requested from the library was now available for download. Well, that clinched it. <br /><br />And so, in the style of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32929.Goodnight_Moon" title="Goodnight Moon by Margaret Wise Brown" rel="nofollow noopener">Goodnight Moon</a>, I am bidding this book good-bye. Good-bye book. Good-bye hopelessly twee title (which should have been a clue). Good-bye awkward dialogue, and good-bye emotional manipulation. Good-bye, poor cliched struggling immigrant adolescent Henry. Good-bye, clearly doomed age-inappropriate romance. Good-bye, Henry's efforts to dodge the one-dimensional evil bullies. Good-bye, contrived coincidences. Good-bye, stock characters. Good-bye, goodreaders everywhere whose ratings of this book averaged out to 3.9. (3.9!) </span>
